<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#9FA6C4"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000000" FACE="Verdana">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Vito</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">I am at lvl 25 or so smithing, and rusty weapons are trivial.  I know I'm not ready for banded yet, so what do I do to improve at this point (lvl 25-50 smithing)? Also, are the supplies available anywhere near qeynos (or must I go to Highpass Hold or Freeport?)??<P>Vito<BR>15th level paladin<BR>The Rathe server<P>PS I already have plenty of sharpening stones; what I am asking is what I need once I get BEYOND sharpening...<BR><p>[This message has been edited by Vito (edited 10-14-1999).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Lothlin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Hello Vito,<P>Just saw your thread, and I posted the following reply to effectively the same question from Halas:Lothlin<BR>unregistered   posted 10-12-1999 04:47 PM            <BR>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<BR>Good News/Bad News: Sharpening Stones are available in Qeynos when someone else brings them in from Freeport. Anticipate a cost of 1 pp per 20 stones. Not cheap since they sell for 3cp in Freeport, but if you're ever done that trip without SOW, you'll agree to the price. I have looked for other ways of practising Smithing at the low levels on other chats and finally made the run Camo'd(Druid 5th level spell). One death and one near-death experience, purchased the stones and Gated (D.9th) back immediately.<BR>I've shown you the two options that I am aware of, and wish you Luck with either.<P><BR>------<BR>Good Luck to you also, Vito<P>Lothlin, Druid of the 10th, Innoruuk<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Bard Valmi (Tunare)</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Borrow a Bard!  I'm a Bard of 11th level and now make the run to HPass on a regular basis.  Bards (or anyone) can do a quest running mail to and from HighPass.  This will pay for the stones, and a little extra sometimes.  I've made as much as 16gp from one mail drop (it's random).  Find a Bard with a drum and Selo's (Speed song) and it's faster than SOW.  A young Bard should appreciate the protection, just stay close to the river, and away from bears & Griffs (they find Bards very tasty, I know).  If you're on Tunare, give a tell; I love to travel.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Vito</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">I've done the trip to Freeport and got about 350 sharpening stones; <B>sharpening's now trivial for me.</B> What do I practice next to get improves, and are the supplies for the next step available around qeynos?<P>Vito<BR>15th level Paladin<BR>the Rathe server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Paldor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">I have noticed that many of you keep refering to freeport as the nearest suppiles for smithing from Qeynos,  That is actually fase, as you CAN buy them in HighHold Castle.. The location is the Miner NPC very near the HighKeep Banker.  THe problem is that HighHold Pass has nasty 20+ level Orcs and Gnolls, and the Miner is near the Pickclaw Goblins (22-30+ level)<P>You can get molds in the Karanas.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Bard Valmi (Tunare)</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Clarification: Molds available in Qeynos hills for Scalers (Best way to improve after Sharpening stones).  Highpass Keep is closest supply of ore.  You need the stackable pieces of ore to make "Metal Bits" that you will use to make Scalers.  I always buy as many as I can afford and lug them around the corner to the bank and RUN back to Qeynos.  There is a forge in HPass, but its easy to get jumped by gnolls or bandits while looking for it.  You can use just metal bits, scalers and skewers for quite a while.  You can make studs from metal bits and (if market supports) sell them to Tailors.  Trick is with stones or pieces of ore; buy & bank as much as you can at once!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Kaelah</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">I have been making the trek to Highpass for some time now to get sharpening stones.  While there I also looked for ore, but never found any.  could someone please give me an idea as to where the ore is?  The miner didn't have any.  </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</FONT>
